dcterms:description: The ChEMBL bioactivity database provides information on the bioactivity of compounds against various biological targets, which is used to analyze drug-protein interactions.

dcterms:description: ECFP features are high-dimensional chemical fingerprints used to represent compounds in a way that captures their structural properties relevant to their interaction with proteins.

dcterms:description: Position-specific frequency matrices (PSFM) are used to create feature vectors for proteins, summarizing the frequency of amino acids at each position in a sequence alignment.
